{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2022-1628","published":"2022-05-11T11:03:43Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:17:01.178315Z","upstream":["CVE-2020-16117"],"summary":"evolution-data-server security update","details":"The evolution-data-server package provides a personal information management application that provides integrated mail, calendaring and address book functionality. The evolution-data-server package provides a single database for common, desktop-wide information, such as a user's address book or calendar events.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nIn GNOME evolution-data-server before 3.35.91, a malicious server can crash the mail client with a NULL pointer dereference by sending an invalid (e.g., minimal) CAPABILITY line on a connection attempt. This is related to imapx_free_capability and imapx_connect_to_server.(CVE-2020-16117)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"evolution-data-server","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP1","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/evolution-data-server&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"3.30.1-4.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["evolution-data-server-3.30.1-4.oe1.aarch64.rpm","evolution-data-server-debuginfo-3.30.1-4.oe1.aarch64.rpm","evolution-data-server-debugsource-3.30.1-4.oe1.aarch64.rpm","evolution-data-server-devel-3.30.1-4.oe1.aarch64.rpm","evolution-data-server-perl-3.30.1-4.oe1.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["evolution-data-server-doc-3.30.1-4.oe1.noarch.rpm","evolution-data-server-langpacks-3.30.1-4.oe1.noarch.rpm"],"src":["evolution-data-server-3.30.1-4.oe1.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["evolution-data-server-3.30.1-4.oe1.x86_64.rpm","evolution-data-server-debuginfo-3.30.1-4.oe1.x86_64.rpm","evolution-data-server-debugsource-3.30.1-4.oe1.x86_64.rpm","evolution-data-server-devel-3.30.1-4.oe1.x86_64.rpm","evolution-data-server-perl-3.30.1-4.oe1.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2022-1628.json"}},{"package":{"name":